}} Piotr Niesporek\n| PTS || 6 \n|2006-11-11 || align=left|{{flagicon|ROM}} [[R\u00e2mnicu V\u00e2lcea]]\n|align=left|\n|-align=center\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|2-0\n|align=left|{{flagicon|TAN}} Akida Yazidu\n| KO || 3 (4)\n|2006-07-21 || align=left|{{flagicon|ROM}} [[Timi\u0219oara]]\n|align=left|\n|-align=center\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|1-0\n|align=left|{{flagicon|BUL}} Nikolai Mihailov\n| PTS || 4\n| 2006-05-19 || align=left|{{flagicon|ROM}} [[Br\u0103ila]]\n|align=left|\n|-align=center\n{{s-end}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{boxrec|id=358804}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Simion, Viorel}}\n\n[[Category:Romanian professional boxers]]\n[[Category:Featherweight boxers]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1981 births]]\n[[Category:Olympic boxers of Romania]]\n[[Category:Boxers at the 2004 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Romanian male boxers]]\n[[Category:AIBA World Boxing Championships medalists]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Romanian boxer}}\n{{Infobox boxer\n|image=\n|caption= Simion (right) at the [[Romexpo|Romexpo Dome]]\n|name= Viorel Simion\n|realname= Viorel Simion\n|nickname= Bombardierul (Bomber)\n|weight= [[Featherweight]]\n|height= {{height|ft=5|in=5}}\n|reach=\n|nationality= [[Romanians|Romanian]]\n|birth_date= {{Birth date and age|1981|10|19}}   \n|birth_place=  \n|death_date=\n|death_place=\n|style= [[Orthodox stance|Orthodox]]\n|total=25\n|wins=22\n|KO=9\n|losses=3\n|draws=0\n|no contests=\n|medaltemplates=\n{{Medal|Sport | Men's amateur [[boxing]]}}\n{{Medal|Country | {{ROM}} }}\n{{Medal|Competition|[[World Amateur Boxing Championships|World Amateur Championships]]}}\n{{Medal|Bronze| [[2005 World Amateur Boxing Championships|2005 Mianyang]] | Featherweight}}\n{{Medal|Competition|[[European Amateur Boxing Championships|European Amateur Championships]]}}\n{{Medal|Bronze| [[2002 European Amateur Boxing Championships|2002 Perm]] | Featherweight}}\n}}\n\n'''Viorel Simion''' (born October 19, 1981)<ref name=BR>{{cite news| url=http://boxrec.com/list_bouts.php?human_id=358804&cat=boxer | work=boxrec.com | title=Viorel Simion | date=May 29, 2011}}</ref> is a [[Romania]]n professional [[Boxing|boxer]].\n\n== Amateur highlights ==\nAs an amateur, Simion won two bronze medals, at the [[2005 World Amateur Boxing Championships|2005 World Boxing Championships]] in [[Mianyang|Mianyang, China]] and at the [[2002 European Amateur Boxing Championships|2002 European Boxing Championships]] in [[Perm|Perm, Russia]]. He also represented Romania at the [[Boxing at the 2004 Summer Olympics \u2013 Featherweight|2004 Summer Olympics]] in [[Athens, Greece]] also as a [[featherweight]]. \n\n== Professional record ==\n{{s-start}}\n|-\n|align=\"center\" colspan=8|'''22 Wins''' (9 knockouts, 13 decisions), '''3 Losses (1 knockout, 2 decisions)''', '''0 Draws'''<ref name=BR/>\n|-\n|align=center style=\"border-style: none none solid solid; background: #e3e3e3\"|Res.\n|align=center style=\"border-style: none none solid solid; background: #e3e3e3\"|Record\n|align=center style=\"border-style: none none solid solid; background: #e3e3e3\"|Opponent\n|align=center style=\"border-style: none none solid solid; background: #e3e3e3\"|Type\n|align=center style=\"border-style: none none solid solid; background: #e3e3e3\"|Rd., Time\n|align=center style=\"border-style: none none solid solid; background: #e3e3e3\"|Date\n|align=center style=\"border-style: none none solid solid; background: #e3e3e3\"|Location\n|align=center style=\"border-style: none none solid solid; background: #e3e3e3\"|Notes\n|-align=center\n|{{yes2}}Win \n|22-3\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|GEO}} Nika Kokashvili\n|UD || 6\n|2019-04-27\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|HUN}} {{small|Lake Side Hotel, Szekesfehervar, Hungary}}\n|align=left|\n|-align=center\n|{{no2}}Loss\n|21-3\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|USA}} [[Shakur Stevenson]]\n|TKO || 1 (10), {{small|3:00}}\n|2018-10-13\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|USA}} {{small|[[CHI Health Center Omaha|CHI Health Center]], [[Omaha, Nebraska]], U.S.}}\n|align=left|\n|-align=center\n|{{no2}}Loss \n|21-2   \n| align=left|{{flagicon|GB}} [[Scott Quigg]]\n|UD || 12\n|[[Anthony Joshua vs. Wladimir Klitschko|2017-04-29]]\t\n|align=left|{{flagicon|UK}} {{small|[[Wembley Stadium]], [[London]], [[England]]}}\n|\n|-align=center\n|{{yes2}}Win \n|21-1   \n| align=left|{{flagicon|ESP}} Andoni Gago\n|UD  || 12\n|2016-10-14\t\n|align=left|{{flagicon|ROM}} Globus Circus, [[Bucharest]]\n|align=left|{{small|Retained the [[International Boxing Federation|IBF]] Inter-Continental [[Featherweight]] Title.}}  \n|-align=center\n|{{yes2}}Win \n|20-1   \n| align=left|{{flagicon|BEL}} Alexander Miskirtchian\n|UD  || 12\n|2016-03-18\t\n|align=left|{{flagicon|ROM}} Globus Circus, [[Bucharest]]\n|align=left|{{small|Won the vacant [[International Boxing Federation|IBF]] Inter-Continental [[Featherweight]] Title.}}\n|-align=center\n|{{yes2}}Win \n|19-1   \n| align=left|{{flagicon|HUN}} David Kis\n|TKO  || 3 (12) \n|2015-08-28\t\n|align=left|{{flagicon|ROM}} [[Gala\u021bi Skating Rink]], [[Gala\u0163i]]\n|align=left|{{small|Won the [[World Boxing Foundation|WBF]] World  [[Featherweight]] Title.}}\n|-align=center\n|{{yes2}}Win \n|18-1   \n| align=left|{{flagicon|COL}} Franklin Teran\n|RTD  || 3 (8) \n|2014-10-31\t\n|align=left|{{flagicon|GER}} [[Cuxhaven]], [[Lower Saxony|Niedersachsen]]\n| \n|-align=center\n|{{yes2}}Win \n|17-1 \n| align=left|{{flagicon|AZE}} Bakhtiyar Iskenderzade\n| UD || 10  \n|2014-05-16\t\n|align=left|{{flagicon|GER}} CU Arena, [[Hamburg]]\n| \n|-align=center\n|{{no2}}Loss\n|16-1\n| align=left|{{flagicon|UK}} [[Lee Selby]]\n| UD || 12 \n|2013-07-13\n|align=left|{{flagicon|UK}} [[Craven Park, Hull|Craven Park Stadium]], [[Kingston upon Hull|Hull]]\n|align=left|{{small|Lost [[World Boxing Council|WBC]] International [[Featherweight]] Title.}}\n|-align=center\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|16-0\n| align=left|{{flagicon|PHI}} [[Ryan Sermona]]\n| TKO || 4 (12)\n|2012-11-29\n|align=left|{{flagicon|